                <div class="section-title">
                        <h2>Context</h2>                       
                        <p>It seems that sitting for hours on end at work has become the standard these days. In our sedentary work settings, most of us have been sitting for long periods of time each day
                        studying(working) on a computer and don’t even think about giving a rest., that will lead to a risk for developing physical strain and overuse injuries.</p>
                        <p>Executing independently, I conducted user reach and found out that users actually need to be reminded on a regular basis so they can schedule some breaks when they are spending too much time in work, pushing themselves too hard</p>
                </div>
                <div class="section-title">
                        <h2>Process</h2>  
                        <p>I followed the User Centered Design process to investigate how users may want to their experiences based on their preferences. Letting user research be my guide, I designed multiple solutions and then tested the ideas via usability tests and developed a high-fidelity prototype based on my findings.</p> 
                        <div class="card mb-4"><img src="/assets/images/hcd.png" class="img-responsive"></div> 
                         
                                
                </div>                 
                

                <div class="section-title">
                        <h2>Discovery</h2>    
                        <ul>
                            <li >All interviews knew taking breaks are important in recovering from stress, improving performance etc, but sometimes, they were just so busy focusing on things doing and didn’t even think about giving a rest.</li><br/>
                            <li >Top features users are looking for from a smartwatch: Telling time;  Showing/Managing notifications, so that users won’t miss out any important alerts; Added smarts, such as step counting, Track fitness progress, monitoring heart beat</li><br/>
                            <li >Design Requirement : Users stated that they were prefer easier functionalities or user flow. Large tap target , less text and bright colors are suggest, that are easy to perceive and make information legible.</li><br/>
                            <li> How often should I take a break? </li>
                            <div class="card mb-4"><img src="/assets/images/breaktime.jpg" class="img-responsive"></div>  
                            <p>Therefore, the app will come with 2 kinds of break by default: a 15 minutes one every 60 mins and a 20 second one every 20 minutes.
                            Users can pause/resume reminding of breaks, set break duration and interval of break.</p>
                           

                        </ul>                   
                                    
                </div>

             
                <div class="section-title">
                        <h2>Use Cases</h2>                       
                        <p> While analyzing my findings from user interviews, I identified People living a sedentary lifestyle to be the most common use cases or scenarios where users stated they would utilize a solution / reminder to notify
                        themselves to take a break. By saying “SETTING”, they could schedule the breaks based on their daily timeline, and selected the break interval. They could change the break duration by turning the digital
                        crown and pressed START to start the break, or manually paused the break time counting down, when for example anserwing a call.</p>                        
